events.name: Washington Huskies at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Dante Pettis woke up No. 8 Washington just before halftime with his sixth career punt return for a touchdown and Jake Browning threw two second-half touchdown passes in a tougher-than-expected 30-14 victory over rebuilding Rutgers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pettis, Browning lead No. 8 Washington past Rutgers, 30-14

events.name: Utah State Aggies at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: — Wisconsin teammates John Torchio and Braelon Allen created a couple of truly memorable moments in an otherwise forgettable season-opening matchup.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen, Torchio help No. 18 Badgers rip Illinois State 38-0

video.headline: Slow start doesn't stop Wisconsin from onslaught in opener

events.name: Fordham Rams at Army Black Knights

headlines.description: Ahmad Bradshaw rushed for two touchdowns and gained 128 of his 177 yards in the first half as Army crushed Fordham 64-6 in the opener for both teams Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Army: 513 yards, no completions in opening win

headlines.description: Brogan Roback passed for 267 yards, Ian Eriksen ran for two touchdowns and Eastern Michigan opened the season with a 24-7 win over Charlotte on Friday night.

video.headline: Eastern Michigan scores first with pick-six

events.name: Central Connecticut Blue Devils at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Eric Dungey threw for three scores and ran for two more and Syracuse dominated in every aspect Friday night to defeat Central Connecticut State 50-7 in the season opener and first-ever matchup between the schools.

video.headline: Syracuse jumps out to early 14-point lead

tracking.trackingName: COM_Highlight (Syracuse jumps out to early 14-point lead) 09/01/17 ESHEET

events.name: Colorado State Rams at Colorado Buffaloes

headlines.description: Phillip Lindsay ran for 140 yards on 19 carries and Colorado capitalized on a flurry of debatable judgment calls by the Pac-12 officiating crew in a 17-3 victory over Colorado State on Friday night in the Rocky Mountain Showdown.
headlines.shortLinkText: Colorado beats CSU 17-3 behind Lindsay, flurry of flags

video.headline: Colorado's Fields hauls in deep pass for TD

events.name: Navy Midshipmen at Florida Atlantic Owls

headlines.description: Lane Kiffin's debut at Florida Atlantic lasted nearly six hours, featured three lightning delays and ended with almost no one left in the stands.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lightning drags out Kiffin's debut, Navy tops FAU 42-19

events.name: Boston College Eagles at Northern Illinois Huskies

headlines.description: Anthony Brown threw for two touchdowns in his first career start and Colton Lichtenberg's 37-yard field goal with 2:13 to play lifted Boston College past Northern Illinois 23-20 in a season opener on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late FG lifts Boston College past N. Illinois 23-20
